<subSubSection id="F8ACF75E5EEF52106BAE75D561B10160" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="18" pageNumber="67" type="descriptions">
<paragraph id="289CD5997ECE53F37C4C262CA5B3DAFD" pageId="18" pageNumber="67">Descriptions.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="84C2E85C28F1A029981243B07B93154A" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="18" pageNumber="67">
Annual or short-lived perennial herbs, rarely rhizomatous; stems terete and usually striate, with broad solid pith; hairs uniseriate with erect apical cells, with glandular dots. Leaves alternate, sessile or short petiolate; blades thinly 
<pageBreakToken id="C46A425284C3FA496D357F23A9BC6E41" pageId="19" pageNumber="68" start="start">herbaceous</pageBreakToken>
, ovate to linear lanceolate, base cuneate or continuous onto stem, margins subentire to serrate or dentate, apex acute to obtuse, surfaces glabrous to densely pubescent; venation pinnate with ascending secondary veins. Inflorescence terminal, corymbiform to rather cymiform, lower bracteoles a reduced foliiform, peduncular bracteoles filiform. Heads rather small, with broadly campanulate involucres; involucral bracts 15-40 in 2-3 usually subequal series; receptacle flat or slightly convex, epaleaceous. Florets 3-100 in a head, strongly exserted; corollas white or pink to purple, with glandular dots on surface, with a narrow cylindrical base, limb narrowly funnelform to narrowly campanulate; lobes lanceolate, without apical hairs; bases of anther thecae rounded, not tailed; apical appendages glabrous; style base without node; branches with sweeping hairs shortly acute. Achenes cylindrical with 2-6 usually paler ribs, sides with glandular dots, rarely with short white setulae; raphids short-oblong; pappus lacking or a coroniform rim. Chromosome number n = 10, 20 (
<bibRefCitation id="E35CB5F6EC6868C5B928F2234306A8B4" author="Pilz, GE" editor="Loeve, A" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="51" pageNumber="100" pagination="347 - 367" refId="B34" refString="Pilz, GE, 1980. . In: Loeve, A, Ed., IOPB Chromosome number reports LXVII. Taxon 29: 347 - 367" volume="29" volumeTitle="IOPB Chromosome number reports LXVII." year="1980">Pilz 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="7C52ABD49BB5BE1B732400D8D4E23506" author="Gilbert, MG" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="50" pageNumber="99" pagination="165 - 193" publicationUrl="10.2307/4113733" refId="B11" refString="Gilbert, MG, Jeffrey, C, 1988. A revision of Ethulia (Compositae: Vernonieae). Kew Bulletin 43 (2): 165 - 193, DOI: 10.2307/4113733" title="A revision of Ethulia (Compositae: Vernonieae)." url="10.2307/4113733" volume="43" year="1988">Gilbert and Jeffrey 1988</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F3DB59D651CC0F49EF97391FB8B0AB99" pageId="19" pageNumber="68">
Pollen: ca. 35 
<normalizedToken id="83885C840EBD2D8A2DFBA02279C8B83D" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in diam. in fluid; tricolporate, sublophate, echinate, spines long; tectum continuous in intercolpi and at poles, distinctly microperforate; columellae below spines firmly attached to footlayer (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="46F47C4CB44E2E53E353D799372CA356" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Scanning electron micrographs of acetolyzed echinolophate pollen of Erlangea and sublophate pollen of Ethulia. A-C Erlangea misera (Oliv. &amp; Hiern) S. Moore. A Poral view B Near polar view C Grain fragment. D-F Ethulia conzyoides L. f. D Equatorial view, showing comparatively blunt spines E Lateral view F Grain fragment. (D-F Funk 12708 G Petelot 4047 H Lewis 6025; Ethulia views from Robinson and Skvarla (2010 ))." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.60.6734.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/77480" pageId="19" pageNumber="68">
8 
<normalizedToken id="96E6D29A1E63B46184A8B3ACE235D0D4" originalValue="D–F">D-F</normalizedToken>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5495A493D65FF084FD77983D992C1212" pageId="19" pageNumber="68">
Notable secondary metabolites: 5-alkylcoumarins (
<bibRefCitation id="FDD833A6939691373E7BE0117D0A244E" author="Bohlmann, F" journalOrPublisher="Plant Systematics and Evolution" pageId="50" pageNumber="99" pagination="3 - 43" publicationUrl="10.1007/978-3-7091-6928-5_2" refId="B5" refString="Bohlmann, F, Jakupovic, J, 1990. Progress in the chemistry of the Vernonieae (Compositae). Plant Systematics and Evolution 4: 3 - 43, DOI: 10.1007/978-3-7091-6928-5_2" title="Progress in the chemistry of the Vernonieae (Compositae)." url="10.1007/978-3-7091-6928-5_2" volume="4" year="1990">Bohlmann and Jakupovic 1990</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName id="85BC8202B59D10433B32E4D5E7B11A2E" authorityName="L. f. subsp. conyzoides" authorityYear="1762" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Ethulia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ethulia conyzoides" order="Asterales" pageId="19" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conyzoides">
<emphasis id="121DA4B0423AA17E40BE8ED6532D496E" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="68">Ethulia conyzoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
